Here's your complete MSTest 3.x → 4.x migration plan, based on the [official migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/testing/unit-testing-mstest-migration-v3-v4) and your project's specific code:

---

### 1. Upgrade Target Framework (`net6.0` → `net8.0`)
MSTest 4 drops support for .NET 6 and .NET 7. Minimum is **`net8.0`**.

### 2. Switch to MSTest SDK (recommended) or meta-package
Replace the three separate package references with the `MSTest.Sdk` project SDK:
```xml
<!-- Before -->
<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PackageReference Include="MSTest.TestFramework" Version="3.8.0" />
  <PackageReference Include="MSTest.TestAdapter" Version="3.8.0" />
  <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk" Version="17.13.0" />

<!-- After -->
<Project Sdk="MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0">
  <!-- No package references needed -->
```
Remove `<IsPackable>false</IsPackable>` (SDK sets it).

### 3. Migrate `LoggingTestMethodAttribute` (custom `TestMethodAttribute`)
Two changes required:
- **`Execute` → `ExecuteAsync`**: the synchronous `Execute(ITestMethod)` is removed; override `ExecuteAsync` instead (returns `Task<TestResult[]>`).
- **Add caller-info constructor**: propagate `[CallerFilePath]`/`[CallerLineNumber]` to the base.

```csharp
// Before
public sealed class LoggingTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod) { ... }
}

// After
public sealed class LoggingTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public LoggingTestMethodAttribute(
        [CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "",
        [CallerLineNumber] int callerLineNumber = -1)
        : base(callerFilePath, callerLineNumber) { }

    public override Task<TestResult[]> ExecuteAsync(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Starting: {testMethod.TestMethodName}");
        return base.ExecuteAsync(testMethod);
    }
}
```

### 4. Remove `[ExpectedException]` → use `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>`
The `ExpectedExceptionAttribute` is removed.

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_BadInput_Throws()
{
    throw new ArgumentException("bad");
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_BadInput_Throws()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentException>(
        () => throw new ArgumentException("bad"));
}
```

### 5. Remove `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum usage
The `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum is removed; `EndOfClass` is now the only (default) behavior.

```csharp
// Before
[ClassCleanup(ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass)]

// After
[ClassCleanup]
```

### 6. Fix `Assert.AreEqual` format parameters
Overloads accepting `string message, params object[]` are removed. Use interpolation:

```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(1, 1, "Expected {0}", 1);

// After
Assert.AreEqual(1, 1, $"Expected {1}");
```

### 7. Replace `TestTimeout.Infinite`
The `TestTimeout` enum is removed. Use the literal value:

```csharp
// Before
[Timeout(TestTimeout.Infinite)]

// After
[Timeout(int.MaxValue)]
```

### 8. Fix `TestContext.Properties.Contains` → `.ContainsKey`
`Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` (no `Contains` method):

```csharp
// Before
TestContext.Properties.Contains("env");

// After
TestContext.Properties.ContainsKey("env");
```

---

### Summary checklist

| # | Change | File(s) |
|---|--------|---------|
| 1 | `net6.0` → `net8.0` | `.csproj` |
| 2 | Switch to `MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0`, remove packages | `.csproj` |
| 3 | `Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` + caller-info ctor | `IntegrationTests.cs` |
| 4 | `[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly` | `IntegrationTests.cs` |
| 5 | Remove `ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass` param | `IntegrationTests.cs` |
| 6 | `Assert.AreEqual` format params → interpolation | `IntegrationTests.cs` |
| 7 | `TestTimeout.Infinite` → `int.MaxValue` | `IntegrationTests.cs` |
| 8 | `Properties.Contains` → `Properties.ContainsKey` | `IntegrationTests.cs` |

Want me to implement these changes?
